<%#
  Renders a session's agent-root default artifacts as muted, dashed "inherited"
  tags, shown in place of "None" when the session's own catalog column is blank.

  A session freezes its catalog columns (mcp_servers / catalog_skills /
  catalog_hooks / catalog_plugins) at creation. Those can land empty when the
  catalog transiently resolved no defaults for the root, leaving the detail page
  showing "None" forever. These tags surface what the root *currently* declares,
  deliberately styled apart from the color-coded "captured" badges so it's clear
  they were not part of this session's snapshot.

  Locals:
    items [Array<String>] the agent-root default artifact ids
    label [String] short source label, e.g. "agent root default"
%>
<span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 flex-wrap text-xs">
  <% items.each do |item| %>
    <span class="inline-flex items-center px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-medium bg-gray-100 text-gray-500 border border-dashed border-gray-300"
          title="<%= item %>: <%= label %> (not captured in this session's snapshot)"
          aria-label="<%= item %>: <%= label %> (not captured in this session's snapshot)"><%= item %></span>
  <% end %>
  <span class="text-gray-400 italic"
        title="These are the agent root's current defaults, shown because this session captured none.">(<%= label %>)</span>
</span>
